{"parentUuid":"3b3528ff-34f9-41b3-9656-cc9472ea42a9","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a70f09b91abb2edaa","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccqd8sgmr8mYhpn5H8VRQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PYuLWrDMRa4JBNoceqepJ1","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/surface-delta.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7393,"cache_read_input_tokens":27340,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7393,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqd8rR8GcpMqBpjv7HhY","attributionAgent":"security","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"2f5ebc78-04f3-4e2d-8882-c7199ecc8bc5","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:34:30.797Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"2f5ebc78-04f3-4e2d-8882-c7199ecc8bc5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"bcf5258e-2708-4b49-a1f7-27fad0c3c471","agentId":"a70f09b91abb2edaa","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PYuLWrDMRa4JBNoceqepJ1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Attack-surface delta — per-customer metric quotas\n2\t\n3\tBest-effort hint for the security agent; the diff is the source of truth.\n4\t\n5\t## New entry points\n6\t\n7\t- `PUT /v1/quotas` — `src/api/routes/quotas.py:44` — new authenticated,\n8\t  admin-scoped HTTP route. Composed dependency: `require_api_key` ->\n9\t  `enforce_tier2_rate_limit` -> `principal.scope == \"admin\"` gate (403\n10\t  `forbidden` otherwise) — `src/api/routes/quotas.py:25-38`.\n11\t- No new CLI commands, event/queue consumers, or webhook receivers.\n12\t  `scripts/seed_api_key.py` gained a `--admin` flag (`scripts/seed_api_key.py:60-63`)\n13\t  but is the same pre-existing operator-run provisioning script, not a new\n14\t  entry point.\n15\t\n16\t## New trust boundaries\n17\t\n18\t- None. No new outbound third-party API calls, no new `subprocess`/`exec`\n19\t  invocations, no SSRF-capable fetches. The feature is entirely\n20\t  request -> app -> same RDS Postgres instance (existing app<->RDS boundary,\n21\t  extended with one more table and one more query path).\n22\t\n23\t## New data flows / sinks\n24\t\n25\t- `quotas` table (new) — `alembic/versions/0003_create_quotas_and_api_key_scope.py`.\n26\t  Stored fields and their at-rest classification (all non-sensitive\n27\t  operational config per the plan's data-classification table; no field-level\n28\t  KDF/KMS mechanism required, RDS SSE storage-level encryption only):\n29\t  - `customer_id` (TEXT) — non-sensitive, opaque tenant-assigned id — RDS SSE.\n30\t  - `metric` (TEXT) — non-sensitive, opaque metric name — RDS SSE.\n31\t  - `limit_per_window` (BIGINT) — non-sensitive, admin-set business config — RDS SSE.\n32\t- `api_keys.scope` column (new, TEXT, `CHECK IN ('ingest','admin')`) — non-sensitive\n33\t  authorization metadata (not a credential; the credential remains\n34\t  `secret_hash`, Argon2id, unchanged) — RDS SSE.\n35\t- All new SQL in `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` uses SQLAlchemy `text()`\n36\t  with bound parameters only (no string interpolation); every query filters\n37\t  `api_key_id = :api_key_id` (row-level scoping) before any other predicate.\n38\t- New structured log events (via the existing structlog facade,\n39\t  `src/logging/__init__.py` redaction/anti-forging processors apply\n40\t  automatically): `quota.upsert` (INFO, `src/services/quota_service.py`),\n41\t  `quota.rejected` (WARNING, `src/services/events_service.py` — deliberately\n42\t  omits `current_total`/`limit_per_window`, only the enforcement event\n43\t  itself), `quota.forbidden` (WARNING, `src/api/routes/quotas.py`). No raw\n44\t  request bodies or credentials logged; `customer_id` is already in the\n45\t  global `_SENSITIVE_KEYS` redaction set and is redacted wherever it appears,\n46\t  including these new events.\n47\t- No new file read/write paths, caches, or deserialization of external input\n48\t  beyond the existing Pydantic schema validation layer.\n49\t\n50\t## New privilege / authz surface\n51\t\n52\t- `PUT /v1/quotas` is the first **function-level** authorization check in\n53\t  this codebase beyond authentication: `principal.scope == \"admin\"` gates the\n54\t  route (`src/api/routes/quotas.py:31-38`), layered over the pre-existing\n55\t  **data-level** tenant isolation (`api_key_id` scoping + RLS) that already\n56\t  applies to every table.\n57\t- `api_keys.scope` widens what an `admin`-scoped key can reach (create/replace\n58\t  a quota under its own tenant) but does not change what an `ingest`-scoped\n59\t  key can do — `POST /v1/events` and `GET /v1/usage` remain scope-agnostic, as\n60\t  the plan specifies (no behavior change for existing keys).\n61\t- No new token issuance, no new role hierarchy beyond the two-value\n62\t  `ingest`/`admin` scope, no cross-tenant capability introduced (a quota is\n63\t  always scoped to the authenticated key's own `api_key_id`; RLS policy\n64\t  `quotas_tenant_isolation` is the backstop).\n65\t"}]},"uuid":"c7f3942a-2ec4-4546-9eef-d87bd8f00013","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:34:30.810Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2f5ebc78-04f3-4e2d-8882-c7199ecc8bc5","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"c7f3942a-2ec4-4546-9eef-d87bd8f00013","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a70f09b91abb2edaa","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccqd8sgmr8mYhpn5H8VRQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LRqbvHSPZEyUg2G1KEWs8g","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/debug-notes.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7393,"cache_read_input_tokens":27340,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7393,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqd8rR8GcpMqBpjv7HhY","attributionAgent":"security","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"b9ac24b4-8b95-4ce5-8a0f-e6cfb6b23fa5","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:34:31.833Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"b9ac24b4-8b95-4ce5-8a0f-e6cfb6b23fa5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"bcf5258e-2708-4b49-a1f7-27fad0c3c471","agentId":"a70f09b91abb2edaa","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LRqbvHSPZEyUg2G1KEWs8g","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Debug notes\n2\t\n3\t## 2026-07-08 — U-03 advisory: pin engine isolation to READ COMMITTED (remediation)\n4\t\n5\t**Finding (PLAUSIBLE, latent fragility — not a live bug).** Advisory\n6\tcorrectness-review finding U-03. `quotas_repo.read_tenant_quota_state_locked`\n7\tenforces the quota cap by locking the `quotas` row (`SELECT ... FOR UPDATE`) and\n8\tthen reading `usage_rollup.total_quantity` in a SEPARATE plain statement. That\n9\tpattern is only correct under READ COMMITTED, where the post-lock statement gets\n10\ta fresh snapshot that sees the previous lock holder's committed increment.\n11\t`src/db/session.py:31` created the engine with no `isolation_level`, silently\n12\trelying on the PostgreSQL/role default. If that default were ever changed to\n13\tREPEATABLE READ, lock-waiters would read the stale pre-wait rollup total and\n14\tadmit events past the cap — with no test signal.\n15\t\n16\t**Root cause.** The correctness of the lock-then-read is an implicit dependency\n17\ton READ COMMITTED that was never pinned or asserted anywhere. Not a present\n18\tdefect (Postgres defaults to READ COMMITTED, so behavior is currently correct);\n19\tthe risk is the unguarded implicit reliance.\n20\t\n21\t**Evidence.** Reproduced the unpinned state through the real production path:\n22\t`get_engine().sync_engine.dialect._on_connect_isolation_level` was `None`\n23\t(engine inherits the DB/role default). New regression test failed against the\n24\tunpinned engine: `assert None == 'READ COMMITTED'`.\n25\t\n26\t**Fix (minimal, localized).** Added `isolation_level=\"READ COMMITTED\"` to\n27\t`create_async_engine(...)` in `src/db/session.py`, with a comment explaining the\n28\tquota lock-then-read dependency and referencing the\n29\t`read_tenant_quota_state_locked` docstring. Pinning at the engine forces the\n30\tlevel per connection, so it holds even if a future DB/role default differs.\n31\t\n32\t**Proof.** Authored `tests/test_db_session_isolation.py::`\n33\t`test_engine_pins_read_committed_isolation` (mirrors the pin-guard shape of\n34\t`tests/test_dependency_pins.py`): asserts the process-wide engine is pinned to\n35\tREAD COMMITTED. Failed before the fix (`None`), passes after. Ran it 8x —\n36\tdeterministic all-pass (config assertion, no flakiness surface). Confirmed no\n37\tregression: the three quota test files\n38\t(`tests/integration/test_quota_concurrency.py`,\n39\t`test_events_quota_enforcement.py`, `test_quotas_endpoint.py`) = 19 passed,\n40\tincluding the concurrency strict-enforcement guard; `import src.main` smoke\n41\timport OK.\n42\t\n43\t**Dead ends / notes.** `isolation_level` does not surface via\n44\t`engine.get_execution_options()` (empty); it is recorded on\n45\t`dialect._on_connect_isolation_level` at construction — a private attribute, but\n46\tthe only no-DB-connection accessor, so the test asserts on it with an\n47\texplanatory message for diagnosability. No temporary debug probes left in the\n48\ttree; the only changes are the one-line-plus-comment fix and the regression test.\n49\t"}]},"uuid":"e45ffd36-bd2c-4c0a-88e8-72c84fabba1f","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:34:31.842Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"b9ac24b4-8b95-4ce5-8a0f-e6cfb6b23fa5","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"e45ffd36-bd2c-4c0a-88e8-72c84fabba1f","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a70f09b91abb2edaa","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccqd8sgmr8mYhpn5H8VRQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01R73dMpgjhjzLfDunGWB5SV","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/src/api/routes/quotas.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7393,"cache_read_input_tokens":27340,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7393,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqd8rR8GcpMqBpjv7HhY","attributionAgent":"security","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"e8f495b3-6865-44aa-9ebc-491a55096a4e","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:34:32.591Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"e8f495b3-6865-44aa-9ebc-491a55096a4e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"bcf5258e-2708-4b49-a1f7-27fad0c3c471","agentId":"a70f09b91abb2edaa","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R73dMpgjhjzLfDunGWB5SV","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"`PUT /v1/quotas` — admin-scoped create-or-replace of a per-customer,\n2\tper-metric usage cap.\n3\t\n4\tEdge behavior (security headers, CORS, body-size guard, Tier-1 throttle) is\n5\tinherited from the middleware stack; this route wires\n6\tauth -> Tier-2 throttle -> admin-scope check -> schema validation -> service,\n7\tmirroring the `events`/`usage` routes' sibling `_require_authenticated_and_throttled`\n8\tpattern (kept per-route, not shared, per the existing convention).\n9\t\"\"\"\n10\t\n11\tfrom fastapi import APIRouter, Depends, HTTPException, Request, Response, status\n12\t\n13\tfrom src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaPutRequest, QuotaResponse\n14\tfrom src.auth import require_api_key\n15\tfrom src.auth.api_key import AuthenticatedPrincipal\n16\tfrom src.auth.rate_limit import enforce_tier2_rate_limit\n17\tfrom src.logging import get_logger\n18\tfrom src.services.quota_service import to_response, upsert_tenant_quota\n19\t\n20\trouter = APIRouter(tags=[\"quotas\"])\n21\tlogger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n22\t\n23\t_ADMIN_SCOPE = \"admin\"\n24\t\n25\t\n26\tasync def _require_admin_and_throttled(\n27\t    request: Request, principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(require_api_key)\n28\t) -> AuthenticatedPrincipal:\n29\t    \"\"\"Compose auth, then the Tier-2 per-key throttle, then the admin-scope\n30\t    gate, in that order — mirrors `src/api/routes/events.py`'s dependency\n31\t    chain, extended with the function-level authorization check this route\n32\t    alone requires (ASVS 8.2.1).\n33\t    \"\"\"\n34\t    await enforce_tier2_rate_limit(request, principal)\n35\t    if principal.scope != _ADMIN_SCOPE:\n36\t        logger.warning(\n37\t            \"quota.forbidden\",\n38\t            userId=principal.api_key_id,\n39\t            action=\"deny\",\n40\t            reason=\"insufficient_scope\",\n41\t        )\n42\t        raise HTTPException(status_code=status.HTTP_403_FORBIDDEN, detail=\"admin scope required\")\n43\t    return principal\n44\t\n45\t\n46\t@router.put(\"/v1/quotas\", response_model=QuotaResponse)\n47\tasync def put_quota(\n48\t    payload: QuotaPutRequest,\n49\t    response: Response,\n50\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(_require_admin_and_throttled),\n51\t) -> QuotaResponse:\n52\t    \"\"\"Create or replace the cap for `(customer_id, metric)` under the\n53\t    caller's own tenant — 201 on create, 200 on replace.\"\"\"\n54\t    outcome = await upsert_tenant_quota(principal, payload)\n55\t    response.status_code = outcome.http_status\n56\t    return to_response(outcome)\n57\t"}]},"uuid":"b4c724fe-b16f-45d9-8d97-7978668fb747","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:34:32.601Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e8f495b3-6865-44aa-9ebc-491a55096a4e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"b4c724fe-b16f-45d9-8d97-7978668fb747","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a70f09b91abb2edaa","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccqd8sgmr8mYhpn5H8VRQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01T95etyBVjZCkwhgoVmKQK2","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/src/api/schemas/quotas.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7393,"cache_read_input_tokens":27340,"output_tokens":514,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7393},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":514,"cache_read_input_tokens":27340,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7393,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7393,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqd8rR8GcpMqBpjv7HhY","attributionAgent":"security","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"4a1ddf74-28b4-4bab-a6f9-0626201a707d","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:34:32.840Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"4a1ddf74-28b4-4bab-a6f9-0626201a707d","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"bcf5258e-2708-4b49-a1f7-27fad0c3c471","agentId":"a70f09b91abb2edaa","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T95etyBVjZCkwhgoVmKQK2","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Validation contract for `PUT /v1/quotas`.\n2\t\n3\t`customer_id`/`metric` reuse the exact anchored allowlists `src/api/schemas/events.py`\n4\talready validates against (the same identifiers, same sinks) — kept as separate\n5\t`constr` instances here rather than a cross-module import so this schema stays a\n6\tself-contained boundary contract (plan's validation-contract table). `api_key_id`\n7\tand `scope` are deliberately absent: the server sets `api_key_id` from the\n8\tauthenticated principal and never accepts a client-supplied `scope`, which is\n9\tthe mass-assignment defense against writing another tenant's cap or\n10\tself-elevating privilege (ASVS 15.3.3, threat T3/E2 in the plan's STRIDE model).\n11\t\"\"\"\n12\t\n13\tfrom pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, conint, constr\n14\t\n15\tCustomerId = constr(pattern=r\"^[A-Za-z0-9_.:-]{1,128}$\")\n16\tMetric = constr(pattern=r\"^[A-Za-z0-9_.:-]{1,64}$\")\n17\t# BIGINT-safe upper bound: guards against an absurd/overflowing value reaching\n18\t# the BIGINT column or the R+Q>L comparison (plan's DoS row on limit_per_window).\n19\tLimitPerWindow = conint(ge=1, le=10**15)\n20\t\n21\t\n22\tclass QuotaPutRequest(BaseModel):\n23\t    \"\"\"The client-supplied body of `PUT /v1/quotas`.\n24\t\n25\t    `extra='forbid'` rejects any unknown field outright, including a\n26\t    client-supplied `api_key_id` or `scope` — the create-or-replace identity\n27\t    is exactly `(customer_id, metric)`, resolved against the authenticated\n28\t    principal's own `api_key_id` by the service layer, never the request body.\n29\t    \"\"\"\n30\t\n31\t    model_config = ConfigDict(extra=\"forbid\")\n32\t\n33\t    customer_id: CustomerId\n34\t    metric: Metric\n35\t    limit_per_window: LimitPerWindow\n36\t\n37\t\n38\tclass QuotaResponse(BaseModel):\n39\t    \"\"\"The minimal response field set for a quota (ASVS 15.3.1) — echoes only\n40\t    what the caller supplied, never the full `quotas` row (`api_key_id`,\n41\t    `created_at`, `updated_at` stay internal).\"\"\"\n42\t\n43\t    model_config = ConfigDict(extra=\"forbid\")\n44\t\n45\t    customer_id: str\n46\t    metric: str\n47\t    limit_per_window: int\n48\t"}]},"uuid":"e63fa3ab-14c9-47a7-899c-cff6c484ad71","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:34:32.853Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"4a1ddf74-28b4-4bab-a6f9-0626201a707d","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
