/modules/data/main.tf:79:                CREATE ROLE meterly_app LOGIN PASSWORD '${random_password.app_db_password.result}' NOBYPASSRLS;\ninfra/modules/data/main.tf:82:        -c \"GRANT CONNECT ON DATABASE meterly TO meterly_app;\" \\\ninfra/modules/data/main.tf:83:        -c \"GRANT USAGE, CREATE ON SCHEMA public TO meterly_app;\" \\\ninfra/modules/data/main.tf:84:        -c \"ALTER DEFAULT PRIVILEGES IN SCHEMA public GRANT SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE ON TABLES TO meterly_app;\"\ninfra/modules/data/main.tf:100:  depends_on = [null_resource.app_role_bootstrap]\ninfra/modules/network/main.tf:90:  iam_role_arn         = aws_iam_role.flow_logs.arn\ninfra/modules/network/main.tf:98:resource \"aws_iam_role\" \"flow_logs\" {\ninfra/modules/network/main.tf:99:  name = \"${var.name_prefix}-flow-logs-role\"\ninfra/modules/network/main.tf:100:  assume_role_policy = jsonencode({\ninfra/modules/network/main.tf:105:      Action    = \"sts:AssumeRole\"\n=== any role separation docs ===\ndocs/decisions/main/acceptance.md:32:| AC17 | **Tenant isolation (IDOR/BOLA):** an authenticated key **B** cannot read or write key **A**'s data — every repo query is scoped by the authenticated `api_key_id` and PostgreSQL RLS is the backstop (app role without `BYPASSRLS`). B querying A's `customer_id` gets B's own zero, never A's totals. | `src/repositories/*`, `src/db/session.py` | cross-owner denial test (two keys) for read and write | ASVS 8.2.2 |\ndocs/decisions/main/plan.md:242:   (`src/db/session.py`). The app connects as a role **without `BYPASSRLS`**, so even a missing\ndocs/decisions/main/plan.md:337:  nightly S3 (Object Lock) archive. Declared in `infra/` — the app role holds no log-delete or\ndocs/decisions/main/plan.md:563:  `SET LOCAL` per request and the run-every-query-in-a-transaction discipline; app role has no\ndocs/decisions/main/plan.md:564:  `BYPASSRLS`. Flagged because DDIA requires the RLS decision be surfaced.\ndocs/decisions/main/plan.md:625:| E1 | Elevation | events/rollup | Valid key reads/writes another tenant's data (IDOR/BOLA) | H | Mandatory `api_key_id` scoping predicate in every repo query (never unscoped) + PostgreSQL RLS `USING (api_key_id = current_setting(...))`, app role without `BYPASSRLS` (`src/repositories/*`, `src/db/session.py`, migration policy) | 8.2.1, 8.2.2, 8.4.1 |\ndocs/decisions/main/plan.md:711:  scoping predicate on every query + PostgreSQL RLS; app role without BYPASSRLS.\ndocs/decisions/main/security-report.md:216:NOBYPASSRLS enforced. All 85 (58+27) are best-practice/hardening warnings or scan\ndocs/system_architecture.md:152:(encryption at rest, private subnets, least-privilege IAM, no `BYPASSRLS`).\n.pipeline/plan.md:244:    **not the table owner** and lacks `BYPASSRLS` (a table owner bypasses non-`FORCE` RLS). The","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"77af136c-bda5-4ea4-8e26-37a804ef1039","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:47:08.680Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"94b272ac-90d7-4360-bcc8-13084ba94a58","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
