{"parentUuid":"70a1aa3b-617b-44ed-96bc-30e806fd301a","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"bcf5258e-2708-4b49-a1f7-27fad0c3c471","agentId":"a70f09b91abb2edaa","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UiBdT63YpnhKmKHZRnfUGY","type":"tool_result","content":"=== alembic env.py ===\n1:\"\"\"Alembic environment — resolves the database URL through the secrets facade\n10:from sqlalchemy.engine import Connection\n14:from src.config.secrets import get_database_url\n24:def _get_url() -> str:\n25:    \"\"\"Resolve the database URL through the secrets facade — never read\n26:    `DATABASE_URL` (or any secret) directly from `os.environ` here.\"\"\"\n27:    return get_database_url()\n31:    \"\"\"Run migrations in 'offline' mode (emits SQL without a live connection).\"\"\"\n33:        url=_get_url(),\n42:def _do_run_migrations(connection: Connection) -> None:\n43:    \"\"\"Configure the migration context against a live connection and run migrations.\"\"\"\n44:    context.configure(connection=connection, target_metadata=target_metadata)\n50:    \"\"\"Run migrations in 'online' mode against a live async database connection.\"\"\"\n52:    configuration[\"sqlalchemy.url\"] = _get_url()\n53:    connectable = async_engine_from_config(configuration, prefix=\"sqlalchemy.\", poolclass=pool.NullPool)\n55:    async with connectable.connect() as connection:\n56:        await connection.run_sync(_do_run_migrations)\n58:    await connectable.dispose()\n=== alembic.ini url ===\n5:# sqlalchemy.url is intentionally NOT set here — env.py resolves the real\n=== migration invocation in infra/deploy ===\ninfra/modules/data/main.tf:22:# bootstrap (below) and by the migration job; the running application never\ninfra/modules/data/main.tf:55:# RLS policies on events/usage_rollup (alembic 0001/0002) are an unbypassable\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:11:#   2. deploy-staging — terraform apply envs/staging → snapshot → migrate → rollout →\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:15:#      migrate → CANARY 10% → 50% → 100% by ALB target-group weights, each step soaking\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:18:# Sequencing per envs plan D2: snapshot BEFORE migrate (backup-before-migrate made\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:20:# Residual (stated): the migrate step needs a network path from the runner to the DB; for\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:27:#   <STAGING_DB_IDENTIFIER> <PROD_DB_IDENTIFIER> <MIGRATE_CMD>\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:108:      - name: Snapshot BEFORE migrate (backup-before-migrate, executable)\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:110:          SNAP=\"pre-migrate-$SHA-$(date -u +%Y%m%d%H%M%S)\"\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:114:      - name: Migrate staging (expand/contract enforced upstream by plan-audit)\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:117:          [ -n \"$DATABASE_URL\" ] && [ \"$DATABASE_URL\" != \"None\" ] || { echo \"staging DB URL not resolved from SSM — refusing to migrate\" >&2; exit 1; }\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:119:          <MIGRATE_CMD>\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:164:      - name: Snapshot BEFORE migrate (prod)\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:166:          SNAP=\"pre-migrate-$SHA-$(date -u +%Y%m%d%H%M%S)\"\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:169:      - name: Migrate prod\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:172:          [ -n \"$DATABASE_URL\" ] && [ \"$DATABASE_URL\" != \"None\" ] || { echo \"prod DB URL not resolved from SSM — refusing to migrate\" >&2; exit 1; }\n.github/workflows/deploy.yml:174:          <MIGRATE_CMD>\nscripts/seed_api_key.py:10:anywhere itself, and the plaintext never lands in a migration file\nscripts/seed_api_key.py:11:(`code-standards` forbids credentials in migration files).","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"dc1b7546-3398-4c3f-8a26-a16c997ecf21","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:47:35.071Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"70a1aa3b-617b-44ed-96bc-30e806fd301a","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","v