{"parentUuid":"14767e68-9b6b-4fc0-95f7-9f100d635898","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a70f09b91abb2edaa","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccqf6mfoDdR3c4g9pmwfT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PDnigENJv3Hh5ZmA664Ru2","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/security-report.md","content":"---\nstatus: clean\nran_at: 2026-07-09T01:59:58Z\nscope: diff\nsince_commit: faabe9d6e59533dd144ce7895881dbe54fd7ddd2\ncritical_count: 0\nwarning_count: 3\nfixed_count: 1\ntotal_findings: 4\nsemgrep_findings: 0\nosv_findings: 2\ncheckov_findings: null\ntrivy_findings: null\n---\n\n# Security report — feature: metric-quotas (`PUT /v1/quotas` + per-customer enforcement)\n\n## Scope\n\nDiff against `HEAD` (`faabe9d`). Change set: new `quotas` route/schema/service/repo,\nAlembic `0003` (new `quotas` table + `api_keys.scope` column), the `POST /v1/events`\nenforcement path, split-token/`scope` plumbing, `READ COMMITTED` engine pin, CORS `PUT`,\n`AppError` envelope code, and the `--admin` seed flag. No `infra/` or `Dockerfile` in the\nchange set → Checkov / Trivy / store-compliance not applicable this pass.\n\n## Tools run this pass\n\n| Tool | Scope | Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| Semgrep (`auto`, `p/secrets`, `p/owasp-top-ten`, `p/python`) | change-set `src/`, migration `0003`, seed script | 0 findings |\n| OSV Scanner | project manifests (`poetry.lock`) | 2 ids (1 vuln, `pytest` — dev/test dep) |\n| Gitleaks (`dir`) | full tree | 126 raw, **0 in the change set** (all in `.venv/` + `.pipeline/`) |\n| ASVS Tier-1 SAST (`asvs-sast.sh`) | change set | 0 critical |\n| Lockfile / supply-chain (`lockfile-check.sh`) | change set | clean (exit 0) |\n| SBOM (`generate-sbom.sh`) | project | not produced (Docker generation timed out; best-effort, non-gating) |\n\n## Complete findings inventory\n\n| # | source | id | severity | exploitable | location | disposition |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | osv | GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g | Medium (CVSS 6.8) | no | `poetry.lock` → `pytest@8.3.4` | action-required |\n| 2 | osv | PYSEC-2026-1845 | Medium (CVSS 6.8) | no | `poetry.lock` → `pytest@8.3.4` | action-required |\n| 3 | manual-6d | RLS backstop inert without FORCE (`quotas`) | Medium | no | `alembic/versions/0003_create_quotas_and_api_key_scope.py:54` | fixed |\n| 4 | manual-6d | RLS backstop inert without FORCE (`events`, `usage_rollup`) | Medium | no | `alembic/versions/0001_*.py:66`, `0002_*.py:67` | reported-only |\n\n`total_findings = 4`. Semgrep(0) + Gitleaks(0 in-scope) + ASVS-SAST(0) + lockfile(0) contribute no rows.\n\n## Fixes applied\n\n**#3 — `quotas` RLS tenant-isolation backstop made effective (added `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`).**\n`alembic/versions/0003_create_quotas_and_api_key_scope.py`.\n\n- *What was wrong:* the migration enabled `ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` + policy\n  `quotas_tenant_isolation` but not `FORCE`. Alembic resolves its DB URL through the same\n  secrets facade the app uses (`alembic/env.py` → `get_database_url()` → the `meterly_app`\n  credential in Secrets Manager, `infra/modules/data/main.tf:98`), and `meterly_app` holds\n  `CREATE ON SCHEMA public` (`main.tf:83`). The role that runs `CREATE TABLE` **owns** the\n  table, and a table owner **bypasses non-`FORCE` RLS regardless of `NOBYPASSRLS`** — so the\n  backstop policy would be inert for the application role. This is exactly the plan's\n  unresolved Open Question 2. (The infra comment at `main.tf:21-23` asserts the migration job\n  uses the master credential, but the actual `env.py` code path contradicts it and the deploy\n  SSM parameter is an unresolved placeholder — so non-owner cannot be relied on.)\n- *Before:* `ALTER TABLE quotas ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` only.\n- *After:* added `ALTER TABLE quotas FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` (with an explanatory comment).\n  Safe for the app path: every `quotas` access runs inside `scoped_transaction`, which\n  `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id`, so the policy's `USING`/`WITH CHECK` predicate passes for\n  the caller's own rows. `FORCE` is dropped implicitly by the `downgrade()` `DROP TABLE`.\n- *Confirmed:* consolidated Semgrep re-scan of the change set after the edit = 0 findings.\n\nNote: this hardens defense-in-depth. The **primary** tenant-isolation control — an explicit\n`api_key_id = :api_key_id` predicate on every `quotas` query — was already present and correct\nin both `upsert_quota` and `read_tenant_quota_state_locked`, so no cross-tenant IDOR was ever\nexploitable; finding #3 concerned the second layer, not the barrier.\n\n## Could not remediate\n\nNone.\n\n## Action required (human decision — not auto-fixed)\n\n- **#1 / #2 — `pytest@8.3.4` vulnerable tmpdir handling** (GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g / PYSEC-2026-1845,\n  CVSS ≈ 6.8 Medium). Local-privilege tmpdir predictability in a **dev/test-only** dependency\n  that is not on the request path. Below the deploy gate's CVSS ≥ 7.0 floor → non-blocking.\n  Safe upgrade: bump `pytest` to the patched line (≥ 8.3.5 per the advisory) in `pyproject.toml`\n  + `poetry.lock`. Dependency bumps are the debugging agent's remit, not security's — reported\n  here only.\n\n- **#4 — `events` and `usage_rollup` also lack `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`** (pre-existing, from\n  migrations `0001`/`0002`, outside this diff's change set). Same owner-bypass reasoning as #3:\n  their RLS backstops are likely inert for `meterly_app`. Not modified here (out of scope, and\n  the prior `main` security report claimed \"NOBYPASSRLS enforced\" without catching the owner-\n  bypass nuance). **Recommendation:** add `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` to both tables in a\n  follow-up migration, or verifiably run migrations as `meterly_admin` and confirm `meterly_app`\n  is a non-owner. The explicit `api_key_id` predicate remains the effective primary control on\n  those tables regardless.\n\n## STRIDE mechanism verification (6d)\n\nAll 10 non-accepted-risk threats from `plan.md` §Threat Model have their named mechanism present;\n2 accepted-risk rows (quota-data-at-rest, hot-row serialization latency) skipped per protocol.\n\n| Threat | Mechanism | Evidence | Efficacy |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Spoofing (non-admin sets cap) | `require_api_key` + admin-scope gate → 403 | `src/api/routes/quotas.py:34-42` | ✓ |\n| Tampering (SQLi) | anchored `constr` allowlist + parameterized `text()` | `src/api/schemas/quotas.py:15-19`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py:57-73` | ✓ |\n| Tampering (mass-assignment) | `ConfigDict(extra='forbid')`; server sets `api_key_id` | `src/api/schemas/quotas.py:31`, `src/services/quota_service.py:39-46` | ✓ |\n| Tampering (TOCTOU) | `SELECT … FOR UPDATE` + single `scoped_transaction`; reject before increment | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py:116-149`, `src/services/events_service.py:86-127` | ✓ isolation pinned READ COMMITTED (`src/db/session.py:41`); lock-then-read correct |\n| Repudiation | structured `quota.upsert` / `quota.rejected` | `src/services/quota_service.py:49-56`, `src/services/events_service.py:110-117` | ✓ |\n| Info disclosure | 3-field envelope; logs omit totals | `src/api/errors.py`, `src/services/events_service.py:105-118` | ✓ |\n| DoS (flood) | Tier-2 per-`api_key_id` token bucket on new route | `src/api/routes/quotas.py:34`, `src/auth/rate_limit.py:136-153` | ✓ keyed on `api_key_id`, not IP-behind-ALB |\n| DoS (absurd limit) | `conint(ge=1, le=10**15)` + BIGINT | `src/api/schemas/quotas.py:19` | ✓ |\n| EoP (function-level) | `principal.scope == 'admin'` gate → 403 | `src/api/routes/quotas.py:35-42` | ✓ |\n| EoP (data-level IDOR/BOLA) | explicit `api_key_id` predicate (primary) + RLS backstop | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py:121,136`, migration `0003` | ✓ primary present; RLS backstop made effective via FORCE fix (#3) |\n\n`stride_mechanisms_verified = 10`, `stride_mechanisms_missing = 0`.\n\nEfficacy checks (U-02): **Topology** — Tier-2 throttle keys on `api_key_id` (not client IP), correct\nbehind the ALB. **DB privilege** — owner-bypass gap on `quotas` found and fixed (#3); `events`/\n`usage_rollup` flagged (#4). **Async runtime** — `quotas` access is all `await`ed async DB I/O; no\nCPU-hard KDF on the loop in the new code (Argon2id verify lives in the unchanged auth path).\n**Contract drift** — `customer_id` is in the log redaction set (`src/logging/__init__.py:30`), so the\nnew `quota.*` events honor the redaction contract; the error scrubber path is unchanged.\n\n## STRIDE delta addendum (6f)\n\nNew/changed surface: `PUT /v1/quotas` (entry point), `api_keys.scope` (authz attribute), `quotas`\ntable (data sink). Every one is already covered by a `plan.md` threat-model entry with a verified\nmitigation (see 6d). No new outbound calls, subprocess/exec, SSRF fetch, deserialization, or\nunmodeled data flow. **No STRIDE gap. `stride_new_threats = 0`; addendum empty.**\n\n## ASVS 5.0.0 verification (6g)\n\nTriggered chapters: V1, V2, V4, V6, V8, V12, V13, V14, V15, V16 (per plan `## ASVS Compliance`).\n`n/a`: V3, V5, V7, V9, V10, V11 (no new crypto surface), V17. L1+L2 verified universally; in-scope\nL3 = V15.4.x (TOCTOU-atomic check-then-act) + V11.2.4 (constant-time compare, unchanged).\n\n- V1 parameterized SQL — `text()` bind params only, no interpolation → met.\n- V2 validation / business-logic limit — `constr`/`conint`/`extra='forbid'` → met.\n- V6 API-key auth — Argon2id split-token `require_api_key` (unchanged) → met.\n- V8 authz — function-level admin gate + data-level `api_key_id` scoping (+ RLS backstop now FORCE) → met.\n- V12 TLS — existing ALB/RDS TLS, unchanged → met.\n- V13 config — secrets via Secrets Manager, no hardcoded credentials → met.\n- V14 data protection — identifiers in body not URL; non-sensitive classification → met.\n- V15 secure coding — minimal response fields (`QuotaResponse`), mass-assignment defense, safe concurrency → met.\n- V15.4.x (L3) — `FOR UPDATE` quota-row lock + single-transaction check-then-increment + pinned READ COMMITTED → met.\n- V16 logging/errors — structured logs, PII redaction, generic error envelope → met.\n\n`l1_l2_missing = []`, `l3_in_scope_missing = []`, `doc_advisory = []`, `waivers = []`,\n`reconciled = true`. No plan-cited ASVS mitigation left unimplemented.\n\n## Input-surface reconciliation\n\n1 input source implemented (`PUT /v1/quotas`), 1 declared. Controls present: validation contract\n(`QuotaPutRequest`) + rate-limit policy (Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`). `uncontrolled = []`, reconciled.\n\n## Data-surface reconciliation\n\nStored fields: `quotas.{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}` + `api_keys.scope` — all classified\n**non-sensitive** operational config/authz metadata per the plan's data-classification table; no\ncredential/sensitive-PII field. At-rest control = RDS SSE (storage-level), no field-level KDF/KMS\nrequired. `sensitive = 0`, `unprotected = []`, reconciled.\n\n## Migration scan (`0003`)\n\n- Downgrade path: present (`downgrade()` drops `quotas`, removes `scope` + its CHECK) → not a finding.\n- Destructive ops: `up` is expand-only (create table + add column with backfilling default); `down`'s\n  `DROP TABLE` is the defined reversibility of a create-migration (schema-only, documented) → not a finding.\n- Injectable SQL: none — all static DDL, no user interpolation → not a finding.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":851,"cache_read_input_tokens":102334,"output_tokens":5012,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":851},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":5012,"cache_read_input_tokens":102334,"cache_creation_input_tokens":851,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":851,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnost