{"parentUuid":"bf33424e-5b2c-40ea-81df-0d36c453b350","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a70f09b91abb2edaa","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcqfZb26Y86GktXedgk1a","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JFgwEj5awuKq2VQxVr3FCh","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/security-report.md","old_string":"| 3 | manual-6d | RLS backstop inert without FORCE (`quotas`) | Medium | no | `alembic/versions/0003_create_quotas_and_api_key_scope.py:54` | fixed |\n| 4 | manual-6d | RLS backstop inert without FORCE (`events`, `usage_rollup`) | Medium | no | `alembic/versions/0001_*.py:66`, `0002_*.py:67` | reported-only |\n\n`total_findings = 4`. Semgrep(0) + Gitleaks(0 in-scope) + ASVS-SAST(0) + lockfile(0) contribute no rows.","new_string":"| 3 | manual-6d | RLS backstop inert without FORCE (`quotas`) | Medium | no | `alembic/versions/0003_create_quotas_and_api_key_scope.py:54` | fixed |\n| 4 | manual-6d | RLS backstop inert without FORCE (`events`, `usage_rollup`) | Medium | no | `alembic/versions/0001_*.py:66`, `0002_*.py:67` | reported-only |\n| 5 | semgrep | github-actions-mutable-action-tag | Warning | no | `.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml:54` | reported-only |\n| 6 | semgrep | github-actions-mutable-action-tag | Warning | no | `.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml:85` | reported-only |\n| 7 | semgrep | dangerous-subprocess-use-tainted-env-args | Error (false positive) | no | `tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py:139` | reported-only |\n| 8 | semgrep | dangerous-subprocess-use-tainted-env-args | Error (false positive) | no | `tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py:290` | reported-only |\n| 9 | semgrep | avoid-sqlalchemy-text | Error (false positive) | no | `tests/integration/test_quota_migration.py:73` | reported-only |\n\n`total_findings = 9` (2 osv + 2 manual-6d + 5 semgrep). Gitleaks(0 in-scope) + ASVS-SAST(0) + lockfile(0)\ncontribute no rows. `critical_count = 0` after remediation; `fixed_count = 1` (#3); `warning_count = 8`\n(all remaining rows are advisory/non-blocking — see per-item rationale).\n\n## Semgrep triage (rows 5–9)\n\n- **#5 / #6 — `github-actions-mutable-action-tag` (WARNING, real).** Two CI steps in\n  `pipeline-ci.yml` reference a mutable `@vN` tag rather than a pinned commit SHA — a supply-chain\n  hygiene finding (a tag can be silently repointed). WARNING severity → advisory, non-blocking.\n  Not auto-fixed (pinning third-party action SHAs is a CI-ownership decision). Recommend pinning to\n  full-length commit SHAs.\n- **#7 / #8 — `dangerous-subprocess-use-tainted-env-args` (ERROR, false positive).**\n  `test_perf_k6_load.py:139,290` launch uvicorn for a load test via **list-form** `subprocess.Popen`\n  (`[sys.executable, \"-m\", \"uvicorn\", ...]`, **no `shell=True`**). The only interpolated tokens are\n  `str(port)` and `str(workers)`, both internal `int()`-coerced values — there is no shell and no\n  argv-splitting, so no command-injection vector exists. Test-harness code, not deployed. Not\n  exploitable → not a blocking critical.\n- **#9 — `avoid-sqlalchemy-text` (ERROR, false positive).** `test_quota_migration.py:73` builds an\n  f-string into `text()`, but the interpolated `columns`/`values` are **static literals** assembled\n  in-function (`\"key_id, secret_hash, label, rate_limit_per_sec\"` / `\":key_id, :hash, …\"`); every\n  actual value, including `scope`, is passed as a **bound parameter** in `params`. No\n  user-controlled interpolation reaches the SQL string. Not exploitable → not a blocking critical.\n\nThe three ERROR rows are recorded with `exploitable: no` and are **not** counted in `critical_count`\n(step-7 exploitability judgment over raw scanner severity); `semgrep_findings` still reports the raw\ncount of 5, reconciled against the artifact."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_